# Shared Field Resolver (`lib/field-resolver.ts`)

All field value resolution, insured name extraction, and template formatting MUST use the shared module.

## Dynamic field pipeline (Admin → Snapshot → Resolution)

The system uses a fully dynamic, admin-configured pipeline. Nothing is hard-coded per insurance product.

### 1. Admin configures packages & fields (`form_options` table)

- **Packages**: `groupKey = "packages"` — each row's `value` is the package key (e.g. `insured`, `vehicleinfo`, `contactinfo`)
- **Package fields**: `groupKey = "${pkg}_fields"` — each row's `value` is the field key (e.g. `lastName`, `companyName`). Field keys are stored WITHOUT the package prefix.
- **Categories**: `groupKey = "${pkg}_category"` — per-package categories (e.g. `personal`, `company`)
- **Accounting fields**: `groupKey = "premiumRecord_fields"` — custom premium columns beyond built-in DB columns

### 2. Policy wizard captures data into snapshots

When a policy is created, form values are saved into `cars.extraAttributes` as:
```json
{
  "insuredSnapshot": { "lastName": "Chan", "firstName": "John", ... },
  "packagesSnapshot": {
    "vehicleinfo": { "values": { "make": "Toyota", "model": "Camry" } },
    "insured": { "values": { "lastName": "Chan" } }
  }
}
```
Form field names use the pattern `${pkg}__${fieldKey}` (double underscore), but stored snapshot keys may or may not include the prefix.

### 3. Field resolver matches keys from snapshots

`resolveRawValue({ source, fieldKey, packageName }, ctx)` routes to source-specific resolvers:

| Source | Data comes from | Key matching |
|--------|----------------|--------------|
| `insured` | `snapshot.insuredSnapshot` | `fuzzyGet` + `prefixedGet` strips `insured__`/`insured_` prefixes |
| `contactinfo` | `snapshot.insuredSnapshot` | `prefixedGet` strips `contactinfo__`/`contactinfo_` prefixes |
| `package` | `snapshot.packagesSnapshot[packageName].values` | `fuzzyGet` + tries `${pkg}__${key}` and `${pkg}_${key}` variants |
| `policy` | Built-in fields: `policyNumber`, `status`, `effectiveDate`, etc. + `documentTracking` | Direct map lookup, falls back to `policyExtra` |
| `agent` | `users` table row for `policies.agentId` | `fuzzyGet` (name, email, userNumber) |
| `client` | `clients` table row for `policies.clientId` | `fuzzyGet` (displayName, clientNumber, etc.) |
| `organisation` | `organisations` table row | `fuzzyGet`, plus special `fullAddress` builder |
| `accounting` | `policyPremiums` rows + admin-configured fields | Resolves by `lineKey` + `fieldKey`; supports `total` aggregation |
| `invoice` | `accountingInvoices` row | Direct switch/case on known invoice fields |
| `statement` | Statement data built from `accountingInvoices` + items | Direct switch/case + `item_` prefix for per-item premium breakdown |
| `static` | Template config | Returns `staticValue` directly |

### Key matching strategy

- `fuzzyGet(obj, key)`: case-insensitive exact match
- `prefixedGet(obj, key, prefix)`: tries `key` → `${prefix}__${key}` → `${prefix}_${key}` → normalized match stripping all prefixes
- Package fields: tries `key` → `${packageName}__${key}` → `${packageName}_${key}`
- Special computed keys: `displayName` (insured), `primaryId` (insured), `fullAddress` (contact/org)

## When to use

| Need | Import from `@/lib/field-resolver` |
|------|-----|
| Resolve a field value from snapshot by source + key | `resolveRawValue(ref, ctx)` |
| Resolve + format in one call (PDF/HTML templates) | `resolveAndFormat(ref, ctx, opts)` |
| Format raw value as currency/date/boolean/number/match | `formatResolvedValue(raw, format, currencyCode, extras?)` (extras: `{ trueValue?, falseValue?, matchValue? }` for boolean/match) |
| Get display name from insured snapshot | `getInsuredDisplayName(insured)` |
| Get insured type (personal/company) | `getInsuredType(insured)` |
| Get name from insured + packages fallback | `getDisplayNameFromSnapshot(snapshot)` |
| Case-insensitive key lookup on any object | `fuzzyGet(obj, key)` |
| Build formatted address from getter | `buildAddressFromGetter(getter)` |
| Get primary ID from insured snapshot | `getInsuredPrimaryId(insured)` |
| Get contact field (mobile, tel, email) | `getContactField(insured, key)` |
| Resolve document number for current template | `resolveRawValue({ source: "policy", fieldKey: "documentNumber" }, ctx)` — requires `documentTracking` + `currentDocTrackingKey` in ctx |

## NEVER duplicate these patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — inline insured name extraction
const last = snap.insured__lastName ?? snap.insured_lastName ?? snap.lastName;
const first = snap.insured__firstName ?? snap.insured_firstName ?? snap.firstName;
const name = [last, first].filter(Boolean).join(" ");

// ✅ GOOD
import { getInsuredDisplayName } from "@/lib/field-resolver";
const name = getInsuredDisplayName(insuredSnapshot);

// ❌ BAD — inline package value lookup with prefix fallback
const val = vals[key] ?? vals[`${pkg}__${key}`] ?? vals[`${pkg}_${key}`];

// ✅ GOOD
import { resolveRawValue } from "@/lib/field-resolver";
const val = resolveRawValue({ source: "package", fieldKey: key, packageName: pkg }, ctx);

// ❌ BAD — inline currency formatting
new Intl.NumberFormat("en-HK", { style: "currency", currency: "HKD" }).format(n);

// ✅ GOOD (for template/snapshot display)
import { formatResolvedValue } from "@/lib/field-resolver";
formatResolvedValue(n, "currency", "HKD");

// ✅ ALSO OK (for accounting UI — different concern)
import { fmtCurrency } from "@/lib/accounting-utils";
```

## Context builders

- `lib/pdf/build-context.ts` → `buildMergeContext(policyId)`: loads full policy data (snapshot, agent, client, org, accounting lines, statement) into `MergeContext`
- `lib/pdf/resolve-data.ts` → `resolveFieldValue(field, ctx)`: wraps `resolveAndFormat` for PDF field mappings

## Scope boundaries

- **Template/snapshot field resolution** → always use `lib/field-resolver.ts`
- **Accounting UI display** (cents → display) → use `lib/accounting-utils.ts` `fmtCurrency`
- **Live form values** (RHF) → use `lib/formula.ts` `resolveFieldValue` (different contract)
- **Date display in UI** → use `lib/format/date.ts` helpers
